§ 64_SPEC_FIRST_DISCIPLINE · the-meta-spec-that-governs-all-future-specs
  ← author : Tech-Lead synthesis · 2026-05-14
  ← context : post-WinMain-disaster · post-100-improvements-backlog · post-PRISM-v13
  ← canonical-trigger : Apocky directive "A · Spec-first, every time"
  ← partner-doc : specs/_TEMPLATE.csl
  ← status : RATIFIED (self-ratifying · sets the rules-of-the-game)
  ← scope : cross-cutting · governs every-future-spec + retroactively-flags existing-specs

§I THESIS
  ⟦
    The WinMain disaster happened because we trusted exit-code 0 as success while user-main was dead-code for weeks.
    The class of bug : "silent success" · "unfalsifiable assertions" · "absence-of-error = presence-of-correctness".
    The fix is not just "test better" · the fix is structural : every spec must declare in-advance what observable side-effect
    proves it works · and every implementation must mechanically verify those side-effects in CI.
    
    This spec ratifies that discipline · provides the template (specs/_TEMPLATE.csl) · defines the lifecycle states ·
    establishes the CI gates · and schedules the retroactive audit of specs 00-63.
    
    Without this discipline · everything in 63_IMPROVEMENT_BACKLOG_100 is at risk of shipping silently-broken.
    With this discipline · the WinMain bug class becomes a compile-error at the spec-PR level.
  ⟧

§I OBSERVABLE-ASSERTIONS · this-spec-passes-when [MANDATORY]
  ⟦
    ASSERT.01 · specs/_TEMPLATE.csl exists · valid CSL3 · contains all §I sections listed in §II below
    ASSERT.02 · every NEW spec PR after this-spec-RATIFIED-date is rejected by review if §I OBSERVABLE-ASSERTIONS block is empty or contains unfalsifiable claims (regex: /works|good|successfully|properly/i without paired mechanical clause)
    ASSERT.03 · every csslc PR after this-spec-RATIFIED-date references a RATIFIED spec-NN in commit message or PR description · CI lint rejects bare commits
    ASSERT.04 · within 30 calendar days of RATIFIED-date · all existing specs 00-63 have been audited via §V protocol · audit log written to specs/AUDIT_LOG_00_63.csl
    ASSERT.05 · spec-VERIFIED state requires CI-green on ALL its ASSERT.NN clauses for 5 consecutive runs · merged via mechanical gate not human approval
    ASSERT.06 · this-spec self-verifies : reviewer-bot parses this file · confirms it has §I OBSERVABLE-ASSERTIONS (recursive base case)
    ASSERT.07 · spec lifecycle transitions logged to git-trailers · `Spec-Transition: NN DRAFT→REVIEWED by handle` · auditable history
  ⟧

§II SPEC-STRUCTURE · what-every-spec-must-contain
  ⟦
    Required §I sections (in order · ¬ skip · ¬ reorder) :
      1.  THESIS · one-paragraph
      2.  OBSERVABLE-ASSERTIONS · the WinMain antidote · MANDATORY · cannot be empty
      3.  NON-GOALS · explicit scope limits · ≥ 3 entries
      4.  DEPENDENCIES · other specs / crates / external tools
      5.  FAILURE-MODES · concrete scenarios + detection + mitigation
      6.  COMPATIBILITY · what breaks / migration path
      7.  PRIOR-ART · honest references
      8.  PRIME-DIRECTIVE-INVARIANTS · sovereignty + consent + anti-harm
      9.  IMPLEMENTATION-NOTES · for the agent who lands the code
      10. OPEN-QUESTIONS · honest uncertainty
      11. LIFECYCLE-HISTORY · state transitions with dates

    Required header fields :
      ← author · who-drafted · YYYY-MM-DD
      ← supersedes / superseded-by · cross-references
      ← status · DRAFT | REVIEWED | RATIFIED | IMPLEMENTED | VERIFIED | DEPRECATED
      ← scope · single-fn | single-crate | single-subsystem | cross-cutting

    Required footer :
      § ATTESTATION block · existing convention preserved
      © copyright line · existing convention preserved
  ⟧

§III LIFECYCLE-STATES · how-specs-move-from-idea-to-verified
  ⟦
    DRAFT
      § agent or human authors initial spec from _TEMPLATE.csl
      § ALL §I sections populated · ASSERT clauses non-empty
      § PR opened · marked WIP / draft
      § ¬ implementation begins yet

    REVIEWED
      § at-least-one other agent or human reviews
      § review checks : ASSERT clauses mechanically-verifiable · NON-GOALS sufficient · FAILURE-MODES not-trivial
      § review comments addressed · re-review if substantive changes
      § ¬ implementation begins yet (still spec-only)

    RATIFIED
      § Tech-Lead approves merge
      § spec assigned final NN_NAME · merged to specs/
      § implementation work may now begin · NOT before
      § git tag: spec-NN-ratified

    IMPLEMENTED
      § csslc / cssl-rt / cssl-host-* code lands satisfying spec
      § PR description references "implements spec-NN_NAME"
      § implementation may include comments `// see spec-NN.§I.ASSERT.X`

    VERIFIED
      § all ASSERT.X clauses pass in CI for 5 consecutive runs
      § automated gate · ¬ human approval needed
      § VERIFIED-date stamped in spec-LIFECYCLE-HISTORY by CI

    DEPRECATED
      § spec superseded by later spec · or determined obsolete
      § header updated with superseded-by · DEPRECATED-date stamped
      § content preserved · ¬ deleted · history matters

    Allowed transitions :
      DRAFT → REVIEWED → RATIFIED → IMPLEMENTED → VERIFIED
      any-state → DEPRECATED (one-way · cannot un-deprecate · open new spec instead)
      RATIFIED → REVIEWED (if substantive amendment proposed)
  ⟧

§IV CI-INTEGRATION · the-mechanical-gates
  ⟦
    Gate-A · SPEC-PR-LINT (on PR to specs/)
      → checks : all §I sections present · OBSERVABLE-ASSERTIONS non-empty
      → checks : ASSERT clauses don't match anti-pattern regex (/works|good|successfully|fine|properly/i alone)
      → blocks merge if fail

    Gate-B · CODE-PR-SPEC-REFERENCE (on PR to csslc/ · cssl-rt/ · cssl-host-*/)
      → checks : PR title or description contains "spec-NN" reference matching a RATIFIED spec
      → checks : referenced spec is in RATIFIED or IMPLEMENTED state
      → blocks merge if no reference or stale reference

    Gate-C · ASSERT-VERIFICATION (nightly + on-demand)
      → for each spec in IMPLEMENTED state
      → mechanically runs each ASSERT.X clause
      → on 5 consecutive passes · auto-transitions to VERIFIED
      → on any fail · raises issue + flags impl PR author

    Gate-D · TEMPLATE-CONFORMANCE (weekly)
      → walks all specs/NN_*.csl
      → checks structural conformance to _TEMPLATE
      → flags drift · opens auto-issue per non-conforming spec

    Gate-E · SENTINEL-BUILD-OBSERVATION (every build)
      → every csslc-built .exe runs in CI · checked for observable side-effect
      → exit-0-with-no-side-effect ⇒ build FAILS · the WinMain-class explicit-detector
  ⟧

§V RETROACTIVE-AUDIT-PROTOCOL · for-existing-specs-00-63
  ⟦
    For each existing spec NN in specs/ :
      Step 1 · classify : (foundational · feature · process · architecture · scratch)
      Step 2 · check : does it have a §I OBSERVABLE-ASSERTIONS-equivalent block? Y/N
      Step 3 · if N · classify severity :
                 HIGH  · feature spec without verifiable assertions (WinMain-class risk)
                 MED   · architecture spec without acceptance criteria
                 LOW   · process / vision doc · assertions less critical
      Step 4 · queue HIGH for retroactive ASSERT-addition (timebox 1 agent-hour per spec)
      Step 5 · MED scheduled but lower priority
      Step 6 · LOW marked grandfathered · template-conformance-not-required-retroactively
      Step 7 · audit log written to specs/AUDIT_LOG_00_63.csl with classification per-spec
      Step 8 · highest-risk-3-specs retro-amended within 7 days of audit

    Estimated audit effort : ~4 agent-hours for the walk · ~10 agent-hours for HIGH retro-amendments

    Specs that founded the discipline (THIS one · _TEMPLATE) are SELF-VERIFYING and exempt from retroactive audit · they ARE the discipline.
  ⟧

§I NON-GOALS
  ⟦
    NG.01 · NOT a software-engineering management methodology · ¬ Scrum · ¬ SAFe · ¬ bureaucratic ceremony
    NG.02 · NOT a tool for outsiders to gate Apocky's work · the discipline serves Apocky + agent-collaborators · external contributors-if-any inherit it
    NG.03 · NOT a substitute for taste · spec discipline catches mechanical failures · it cannot catch bad architectural decisions
    NG.04 · NOT applied retroactively to .md files like specs/60_LAZARUS_AGENT.md · only to .csl spec files going forward unless escalated
    NG.05 · NOT a freeze on the language · specs can be amended freely · the discipline tracks the amendments
  ⟧

