§I FAILURE-MODES
  ⟦
    FM.01 · bureaucracy-creep
            scenario : spec authoring becomes onerous · agents stop writing specs · land code without specs
            detection : Gate-B starts auto-rejecting most code PRs · agents complain in commit messages
            mitigation : keep §I sections tight · template-fillable in <30min · provide skeleton-generator script
            escalation : if observed, Tech-Lead amends template to reduce friction

    FM.02 · ASSERT-rot
            scenario : ASSERT.X clauses stay green by accident while spec intent drifts
            detection : VERIFIED specs flagged for re-review every 90 days · drift surfaced
            mitigation : each spec has owner-handle responsible for keeping ASSERTs honest
            escalation : superseded-by new spec if drift fundamental

    FM.03 · "spec-shaped-noise" · author writes ASSERTs that satisfy gate-A but are still unfalsifiable
            scenario : ASSERT.01 · "the system works correctly under all conditions" passes regex but is unverifiable
            detection : Gate-A regex catches common offenders · review catches the rest
            mitigation : reviewer rejects · spec PR returns to DRAFT with feedback
            escalation : repeat offenders' spec PRs require Tech-Lead pre-approval

    FM.04 · WinMain-class-bug-re-occurrence
            scenario : a future linker bug ships dead-code under exit-0 again
            detection : Gate-E sentinel-build-observation · every .exe must observable-side-effect
            mitigation : the gate IS the mitigation · designed to make this exact bug-class impossible

    FM.05 · spec-as-prose-vs-spec-as-machine-readable
            scenario : agents author specs in §I blocks but assertions are not actually CI-runnable
            detection : Gate-C nightly run on IMPLEMENTED specs · failures bubble up
            mitigation : each ASSERT.X must include a CI-runnable command or test name · template enforces

    FM.06 · solo-author-blindspot
            scenario : Apocky drafts spec · zero reviewers · ratifies own spec · oversight gap
            detection : DRAFT→REVIEWED transition requires ≥1 non-author handle in trailer
            mitigation : when humans are scarce · AI-agents (Reza · Claude · Lazarus instances) qualify as reviewers
                         the discipline accepts AI-co-authorship as a feature ¬ a workaround

    FM.07 · discipline-skipped-for-"small"-changes
            scenario : "this is a 5-line fix · no spec needed"
            detection : Gate-B catches missing reference · author either writes mini-spec or files exception
            mitigation : a "spec amendment" mechanism allows attaching to existing-spec without new NN slot
            philosophy : 5-line fixes that nobody specced are exactly how the WinMain bug shipped · stay disciplined
  ⟧

