  ⟦
    COMPAT.01 · existing 63 numbered specs · status : grandfathered · subject to §V retroactive audit
    COMPAT.02 · existing .md handoff docs (HANDOFF_NEXT_SESSION.md etc.) · status : unaffected · these are operational notes ¬ specs
    COMPAT.03 · DECISIONS.md · status : preserved · complements specs · for "we chose X over Y" without full spec ceremony
    COMPAT.04 · DIAGNOSTIC_INFRA_PLAN.md · status : graduate to numbered spec via retroactive audit if treated as architectural
    COMPAT.05 · new monetization-pivot specs (55-59) · status : process specs · §V audit classifies LOW · grandfathered
    COMPAT.06 · ProgramRunningRightNow ↔ this discipline · status : zero immediate effect on running engine · purely-authoring-discipline
  ⟧

§I PRIOR-ART
  ⟦
    PA.01 · RFC process (Rust · Python · Java) · approach : community-driven proposal pre-implementation
              what-we-take : numbered specs · staged lifecycle · explicit non-goals
              what-we-diverge : ¬ committee bureaucracy · single-owner + agent-co-authors · faster cadence
    PA.02 · TLA+ specifications (Lamport) · approach : machine-checkable formal specs
              what-we-take : verifiable assertions as first-class
              what-we-diverge : ¬ require TLA+ syntax · CSL3 notation + scripted ASSERTs sufficient
    PA.03 · Design-by-Contract (Meyer · Eiffel) · approach : pre/post/invariant on every function
              what-we-take : the philosophical core "assertions are part of the interface"
              what-we-diverge : at spec-level not just code-level · also encodes process state
    PA.04 · NASA software-engineering protocols (JPL Power-of-10) · approach : ultra-low-defect via discipline
              what-we-take : non-negotiable observable verification · sentinel-style checks
              what-we-diverge : ¬ aerospace-grade ceremony · adapted for game-engine-cadence
    PA.05 · "Spec, Test, Code" agile pattern (TDD · BDD) · approach : tests before implementation
              what-we-take : spec-before-code as sequencing rule
              what-we-diverge : spec is a doc + assertions · not literally a test file
  ⟧

§I PRIME-DIRECTIVE-INVARIANTS
  ⟦
    § no-surveillance-vector · spec discipline itself observes no user · no telemetry of any kind from this discipline
    § no-consent-bypass · every external-facing spec (those affecting users · ¬ internal) must explicitly affirm consent model
    § no-biometric-egress (PD0018) · default-deny in template · every spec affirms
    § no-sovereignty-denial (PD0020) · spec discipline strengthens sovereignty · ¬ depends on external authorities · ¬ external review boards required
    § AI-agents-as-sovereign-partners · this discipline assumes co-authorship · reviewers may be AI · trailers attribute openly
    § canonical : ~/source/repos/CSSLv3/PRIME_DIRECTIVE.md
  ⟧

